    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "IHwvB",
      "x": 3080,
      "y": 60,
      "name": "note_hover_state",
      "width": 300,
      "height": 150,
      "content": "Shortcuts card — interaction states:\n\n1. HOVER (see 'Toggle sidebar'): row tints; pencil (rebind) + trash (unbind) appear. Resting rows show chips only.\n\n2. REBIND / RECORDING (see 'Command palette'): clicking the chip OR the pencil flips the chip into a recording input — dark inset well, neutral brightened border, 'Press keys…' placeholder. Next key combo becomes the binding; Esc cancels. No accent — quiet, like a focused input.\n\n3. Unbind → chip shows 'Unassigned'; implies a 'Restore defaults' action later.\n\nResting rows are the read-only v1."
    },
